# Deckdrop V2 — Architecture & Build Plan

**Status:** Active build (started March 15, 2026)
**Built by:** Dagny (AI engineer) + Alex Mohseni
**Goal:** Replace Make.com + n8n with a fully code-based, self-hosted pipeline
**Last updated:** March 15, 2026 — OpenRouter added as unified LLM gateway

---

## What Changed from V1

V1 ran on Make.com + n8n automation. V2 is fully code-based:
- All logic in TypeScript/Node.js on Railway (persistent server, no timeouts)
- Full observability: every API call logged with prompts, responses, costs
- Admin dashboard (served from same Railway service) for managing models, prompts, pipeline config, users
- Exa.ai-based competitor research (replaces Gemini Deep Research — ~10-20x cheaper)
- Dagny (AI) can debug independently: submit URLs, receive PDF output via email at dagnytaggart1997@gmail.com

---

## Architecture Overview

### Services
- **Worker + Admin Dashboard** (Railway): Single Express/Node.js service. Handles webhook, runs pipeline, serves admin UI. No Vercel needed.
- **Database** (Supabase): users, jobs, API call logs, model config, pipeline config, prompt library
- **Email inbound** (MailerSend): catches emails at add@ai.deckdrop.io, webhooks to Railway
- **Email outbound** (MailerSend): sends PDF reports back to users
- **File storage** (Supabase Storage): generated PDF reports

